flowchart LR

  subgraph INTENT["1. Path objective"]
    G1["Turn decision and action truth into authoritative audit and lineage truth for the real-time lane"]
    G2["Keep this path narrower than decision formation, action emission, and archive preservation"]
    G3["Answer where the authoritative append-only record of runtime decisions and outcomes gets created"]
  end

  subgraph ENTRY["2. Entry basis"]
    E1["The entry is not raw RTDL traffic and not generic runtime health"]
    E2["The entry is current-run decision and action truth after the RTDL plane has already crossed its main catch-up boundary"]
    E3["The decision-chain closure opens only after RTDL catch-up closure is green"]
    E4["The run-process then requires three distinct closure elements: decision lane committed, action and outcome evidence committed, append-only audit evidence committed"]
    E5["So this path begins after Group 3's decision and action paths have already produced their own truth"]
  end

  subgraph SPINE["5. Broad route logic"]
    R1["Decision truth + action and outcome truth"]
    R2["Audit append writer"]
    R3["Append-only audit and lineage truth"]
    R4["Later publication and archive consumers"]
    R5["The hot path becomes an authoritative historical truth boundary"]
  end

  subgraph CARRIES["4. What the path carries"]
    C1["Decision identity"]
    C2["Action and outcome identity"]
    C3["Run identity"]
    C4["Lineage links from decision to outcome to audit artifact"]
    C5["Enough provenance for later replay, incident review, and downstream learning support"]
    C6["The explainability posture requires traceability to run identity, context surfaces, feature groups, policy/bundle used, action emitted, audit entry appended, and archive/evidence refs"]
    C7["The audit surface narrows that into lineage completeness from decision to outcome to audit artifact"]
  end

  subgraph LOGIC["6. Logical design reading"]
    L1["The platform treats audit truth as a first-class owned append-only surface"]
    L2["It is not something that can be reconstructed later from side effects if needed"]
    L3["There is a dedicated runtime boundary whose job is to append authoritative audit and lineage truth"]
    L4["The decision chain is not considered committed without it"]
    L5["That makes the current wired system look governed rather than hand-wavy"]
  end

  subgraph SEATING["7. Concrete seating in the current wired system"]
    S1["The copied baseline wired graphs show the audit surface as a distinct deployment in the RTDL namespace"]
    S2["Required run pins flow to that surface"]
    S3["The run-process phase map places decision, action, and audit surfaces together inside the live RTDL decision corridor rather than treating audit as later offline convenience"]
    S4["The broader authority keeps the decision, action, and audit surfaces in the RTDL ownership-logic corridor, with the audit surface retained as a distinct ownership-heavy runtime boundary unless semantic parity is proven elsewhere"]
    S5["The live implementation trail shows the audit surface present in the active RTDL runtime set"]
    S6["Bounded proof snapshots recorded append_success_total, append_failure_total, and replay_divergence_total"]
  end

  subgraph RATIONALE["8. Why the design looks like this"]
    Y1["The platform refuses to let auditability be implied by runtime success"]
    Y2["The decision-chain closure explicitly separates decision, action, and audit into three closure elements"]
    Y3["Audit append is not allowed to hide inside a generic claim that the hot path passed"]
    Y4["The audit surface was deliberately not collapsed into a managed replacement by default"]
    Y5["The broader authority keeps it as custom-runtime until full semantic parity is proven"]
    Y6["The current shape is driven by truth ownership and append semantics, not convenience or simplification pressure"]
  end

  subgraph CONTRACT["9. What larger contracts are shaping this path"]
    X1["The audit component contract defines what this boundary must mean"]
    X2["Append-only behavior under replay and duplicate pressure"]
    X3["Zero replay divergence on the same bounded basis"]
    X4["Lineage completeness, bounded unresolved-lineage age, and readback integrity"]
    X5["The decision-chain closure contract says there is no decision-chain closure without append-only audit evidence"]
    X6["The append-only ownership law says append-only ownership violations are stop-the-line conditions"]
    X7["So the platform is treating this as hard truth boundary, not soft reporting surface"]
  end

  subgraph TRADEOFFS["10. Trade-offs and constraints"]
    T1["This path deliberately adds another explicit truth boundary to the hot path"]
    T2["That costs complexity because the system must preserve append-only discipline, duplicate and replay safety, lineage completeness, unresolved-lineage surfacing, and readback integrity"]
    T3["It also explains why the audit surface has not simply been replaced with a cheaper generic sink yet: semantic parity is prioritized over simplification"]
    T4["But that cost buys something important: later case handling, evidence sinks, replay, and learning do not need to infer audit history from scattered clues"]
    T5["They can depend on a named append-only audit boundary"]
  end

  subgraph NECESSITY["11. Necessity test"]
    N1["If this path is removed, the platform can still ingest traffic, build context, materialize features, classify guardrail posture, form decisions, and emit actions"]
    N2["But it loses a clean answer to where authoritative runtime audit truth comes from"]
    N3["It loses a clean answer to whether lineage from decision to outcome is durably preserved"]
    N4["It loses a clean answer to whether replay divergence is visible"]
    N5["It loses a clean answer to whether later reviewers are reading true audit record or just reconstructing history from fragments"]
    N6["That would weaken A immediately because the system would have runtime behavior but no explicit owner for the append-only truth that makes that behavior explainable later"]
    N7["Without the audit surface, you may have decisions but not authoritative audit truth"]
  end

  subgraph CLOSURE["3. Owned outcome and 12. What this path proves for A"]
    O1["Append-only audit and lineage truth for the current run and current runtime event chain"]
    O2["This path closes when the real-time lane has an authoritative audit append"]
    O3["It does not yet include later audit-topic handoff or archive preservation"]
    O4["Owned outcome: append-only audit truth"]
    A1["Purpose claim:<br/>the platform has a distinct job for appending authoritative runtime audit and lineage truth"]
    A2["Intentionality claim:<br/>audit append is a required closure element in the decision chain, not an optional afterthought"]
    A3["Materialization claim:<br/>the audit surface is concrete live runtime workload in the RTDL plane, not just a conceptual box"]
    A4["Contract claim:<br/>this path is governed by append-only discipline, replay-divergence expectations, lineage completeness, and readback integrity"]
    A5["Constraint-awareness claim:<br/>the system already knows this boundary is semantically delicate, which is why the audit surface is retained as custom-runtime until managed replacement can prove full parity"]
    A6["Material participation evidence:<br/>bounded RTDL proof recorded append_success_total = 2494, append_failure_total = 0, replay_divergence_total = 0 as evidence the boundary is real, active, and instrumented"]
    A7["A-level meaning:<br/>runtime behavior becomes authoritative append-only audit truth instead of leaving later reviewers to reconstruct history from fragments"]
  end

